<book id="async-methods">
    <bookinfo>
        <title>Asynchronous Methods</title>
        <subtitle></subtitle>
        <issuenum>${content.version}</issuenum>
        <pubdate>${docbook.pubdate}</pubdate>
        <copyright>
            <year>${copyright.year}</year>
            <holder>${copyright.holder}</holder>
        </copyright>
        <abstract>
            <para>This presentation provides an introduction to using Asynchronous
            Methods in JavaEE.
            </para>
        </abstract>
        
    </bookinfo>

    <preface id="async-methods-purpose">
        <title>Purpose</title>
        <section id="async-methods-purpose-goals">
            <title>Goals</title>
            <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                <listitem><para>Decouple called execution from client thread</para></listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>

        <section id="async-methods-purpose-objectives">
            <title>Objectives</title>
            <para>At the completion of this topic, the student shall be able to:</para>
            <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
                <listitem><para>Define an EJB method to complete in an asynchronous thread</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>Invoke an asynchronous method</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>Check on the completion status of an asynchronous method</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>Return a result from an asynchronous method</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>Compare use of asynchronous methods versus JMS</para></listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>
    </preface>


